.TH UTILITYSCRIPT 1
.SH NAME
UtilityScript.sh \- categorise files and generate UUIDs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./UtilityScript.sh
[\fB\-c\fR \fOUTPUT\fR]
[\fB\-u\fR \fVERSION\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B UtilityScript
has the options to either categorise a file _Directory and it's subdirectories, or generate a UUID version 1 or 4.
.TH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-output =\fIOUTPUT\fR
Determines where the results of the file categorisation are diplayed. Use file to output just to a new file categorise_directory.txt, or terminal to display result to terminal.
.BR \-u ", " \-\-version =\fIVERSION\fR
Set the version of UUID to be generated. Options are either 1 for UUID 1 (time-based) or 4 for UUID 4 (randomly generated).
